OL,3,CTroublemaker turned hero who helps
OL,4,Chomeless people off the streets
OL,6,FJoe said: "It's a bit like a dark
OL,7,Fdungeon of a night time. It's a bit
OL,8,Fscary to be fair.
OL,10,F"It's basically just a cold floor. All
OL,11,Fthe windows are smashed, it's cold."
OL,13,FDylan liaises with housing officers at
OL,14,FWirral Borough Council, and contacts
OL,15,Fout-of-hours Housing Options after
OL,16,Fspeaking with people he has met.
OL,18,FJoe had been sleeping in the house for
OL,19,Fnearly three years, after losing his
OL,20,Fjob and struggling with the passing of
OL,21,Fhis father.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
